**Problem**
When a path component used in the `_.set` method contains a number, lodash will incorrectly create an array of that size. 

**Steps to reproduce**

``` javascript
var bla = {
  test: "ok",
  200: "ok"
};

console.log(_.get(bla, '200', 'fail'));
console.log(_.get(bla, 'test', 'fail'));

_.set(bla, 'bla.200.bla', 'wow');

console.log(_.get(bla, 'test.200', 'fail'));
console.log(bla);
```

**Expected result**

``` json
{
  "test": "ok",
  "200": "ok",
  "bla": {
    "200": {
      "bla": "wow"
    }  
  }
};
```

**Actual result**

``` json
{
   "200":"ok",
   "test":"ok",
   "bla":[
      null,
      null,
      ... [198 more nulls]
      {
         "bla":"wow"
      }
   ]
}
```

